
<p>
  To change the theme of a blog, first extract the content of the theme archive to the directory with the BlazeBlogger repository:
</p>

<pre>~]$ <strong>tar xfz <em>theme</em>.tar.gz</strong></pre>

<p>
  Then move the template file and the corresponding style sheet to <code>.blaze/theme/</code> and <code>.blaze/style/</code> respectively:
</p>

<pre>~]$ <strong>mv <em>theme</em>.html .blaze/theme/</strong>
~]$ <strong>mv <em>theme</em>.css .blaze/style/</strong></pre>

<p>
  Finally, change the configuration to use this theme:
</p>

<pre>~]$ <strong>blaze-config blog.theme <em>theme</em>.html</strong>
~]$ <strong>blaze-config blog.style <em>theme</em>.css</strong></pre>

<p>
  The changes will take effect next time you run the <code>blaze-make</code> command.
</p>

